Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: -Angular Distributions for N-P Scattering In The Energy Range 22.5 To 110Mev -.

x4codes.hlp: Atomic Energy Research Establishment (AERE), Harwell, United Kingdom
Univ. of Oxford, Oxford, United Kingdom

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Conf.Nucl.Forces and Few-Nucleon Probl.,London 1959, p.99 (1959)

x4freetext: -ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS FOR N-P SCATTERING IN THE
PROTON BEAM FROM CYCLOTRON DEFLECTED ONTO A
THICK ALUMINIUM TARGET TO PRODUCE NEUTRON PULSES AT
5 MS INTERVALS WITH DURATION 16 N-SEC AND FWHM OF
TIME OF FLIGHT, ENERGY RESOLUTION 3.5 PERCENT
AT 20 MEV AND 12 PERCENT AT 120 MEV.
LIQUID SCINTILLATOR, 4 G/L OF P-TERPHENYL AND
0.2 G/L OF POPOP DISSOLVED IN TOLUENE. THIS DETECTOR
WAS AT 2 METERS FROM THE SCATTERING SAMPLE AND WAS
USED IN ANTI-COINCIDENCE WITH A THIN PLASTIC
THE THIN PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR WAS USED ALONE TO
DETECT RECOIL PROTONS FOR THE ANGULAR RANGE FROM
.DATA RECOMPILED FROM NEUDADA AND FROM NP,41,401.
.CORRECTION BY DIFFERENCE METHOD FOR CARBON SCATTERING
TO THE NEUTRON MEASUREMENTS WITH AN OVERALL STATISTIC
STATISTICAL COUNTING ERRORS. FOR DETAILS SEE
SYSTEMATIC ERROR IN THE RELATIVE VALUES
SYSTEMATIC ERROR IN THE NORMALIZATION OF THE
SYSTEMATIC ERROR IN THE NORMALIZATION BETWEEN
THE TWO SETS OF PROTON RESULTS.
